,Recommended,281920,29657842,Posted: 2 February,all,BigWoz9,"I'm relatively new to using steam for anything other than FM, but have recently fell into the trap of trawling through the specials and sales when they crop up. I stumbled across this game and almost turned a blind eye due to it being 15p! YES! 15p! Now I do casual gaming, but im not an expert. For it's price, even at full amount, this game is an absolute steal. I like the look of top down shooters and this one really doesnt disappoint. I've only invested the last 2 hours into this game, but I was so pleasantly surprised that I thought I better make this game my first review. There is a loose story line, which so far pretty much fits your stereotypical zombie genre. The character you play as is pretty badass and the level blood and guts is there with every kill. I've played Hotline Miami recently and thoroughly enjoyed it, this has a similar feel to it, but with more enemies, leveling up and combined with a great looking backdrop. This review might not help the hardcore gamer, but for people relatively new to steam and indie games, this is the kind of stuff you're looking for, in fact, for 15p this is what everyone is looking for!"
76561198043835726,Recommended,281920,33095622,Posted: 1 July,all,The_Monk,"While the game feels a bit short, Splatter is just what it promises: a top down shooter with plenty to kill and some people to help (or not) along the way. You start your game with a small variety of weapons but as you advance more and more weapons will become available as well upgrading the ones you already own.Considering its very low price it ended being quite a nice surprise. The story may now be remarkable and the main character often feel cheesy from my own perspective but in the end what matters is that the game feels satisfying to play. It's easy to start and it will leave you curious thinking what's happening in the next location or if the people from a certain village will survive or not.The game can be finished in less than 5 hours but its lenght will depend on what difficulty you are playing. If you want more out of game after completing the main story there is also an arcade mode to test your skills and compete for your spot in the leaderboards as well local co-op for you to enjoy with your friends."
