,Recommended,281920,10413787,"Posted: 9 June, 2014",all,Goldenkitten,"Splatter is a brilliantly crafted top-down shooter that mixes the best of the genres game mechanics with a solid story straight out of a (purposefully) B-grade zombie movie. It operates on a simple concept; did you ever want your top-down to be less pure action and more gloomy ambience and storytelling? If you said yes then Splatter is for you, but if you said no you should probably move on as a large part of the game is devoted to telling a story and building an air of tension.Pros- Tight controls.- Varied Weapons.- Progressive weapon upgrades.- Incredibly rich and engrossing ambiance.- Deep story (for the genre) that even includes optional bits.- Solid length (around 6 hours) with extensive replayability (and achievements for those that care) .- Good soundtrack.- Leaderboards (again, for those who care).Cons- Dumb enemy AI is dumb (but made up for with intelligent level design that takes advantage of their usual blind charge).- Some weapons are blatantly better, meaning some sit about and are never used.- While the graphics themselves ARE nice, I’m not fond of the film-noir filter that grey-scales your surroundings.- Unstable difficulty flailing between painfully easy and crushingly difficult (mostly notable on the hardest difficulty during “defense” missions).In short the positives the game has are far greater than its negatives and it’s definitely worth your time. I recommend it to anyone who enjoys the genre, especially if they’re also fans of the super cheesy but fun classic zombie movies. With good gameplay, a fun story, and a high degree of replayability anyone with a passing interest in the genre will get their monies worth and an experience to remember."
