,Recommended,281920,33365270,Posted: 7 July,all,Setari,"So I'm going to write an extensive review for this, because I believe these devs deserve some more money than they're selling this game for. More than 0.49 cents USD anyway.Gameplay:Gameplay is typical run n' gun gameplay, top down. I don't normally play top down shooters but they did a pretty great job with this one. There are several guns to collect throughout the game as well as secrets hidden in every level, and they do a pretty good job of hiding them too. I've only played a little bit so far but from what I have played, it's pretty good. The weapon upgrades actually help you fight the larger hordes of zombies that are constantly coming at you. There is also pretty decent enemy variety, runners, large zombies, LARGER ZOMBIES, and at the end of my session tonight I ran into zombies shooting fireballs.These aren't the typical Romero zombies or 28 Days Later zombies, they're from a chemical spill or something like that, so I'll give them a pass to use any kind of zombie they really want to at that point. Zombie origins are everything!Shooting mechanics are great as well and with the wide variety of guns, it's pretty fun to be able to switch guns on the fly to gun down a LARGE zombie with a grenade launcher, dodging their shockwaves of them hitting the ground and switching to the pistol for the small fry. I am extremely thankful the pistol has infinite ammo and is upgradeable as well (At least on the easiest difficulty, I don't know about the other ones).  Also, there's no reloading mechanic, which is great for a game like this. Seriously if that mechanic was in this game it'd be 100% harder even on the difficulty I'm playing on.Sound: Sound in the game is fantastic, as is the voice acting in my opinion. Though I pretty much like any voice acting unless it's REEEEEEEEEALLY bad, so. The explosions from explosive barrels sound great as well as car explosions actually being rattling when they happen. Also gun sounds are great.Characters and Storyline: The storyline in the game is not rushed per se but it shoves you into the role of this dude chilling in his house, when he hears a guy yelling ""STOP,"" etc and then a zombie busts through your front door and the SWAT guy shoots it. It goes from there pretty much just the character being on the run from the zombies (Not sure if the character has a name, if he does, I forgot it). There's some pretty interesting parts in the story so far, and from the weapon upgrades I'm getting, I'm pretty sure I'm barely into the game yet, but we'll see I suppose. The characters are very well voiced IMO and are worth listening to, they did a good job with voicing and the slight character development of the NPCs, of the limited time you're with them, and the character development of the main character, what there is anyway. He's pretty much already solidified as a ""man's man"" mentality but it keeps in character, which I can appreciate.Well, generally I think that's it so I do recommend this game if you're looking for a fun time waster that's a zombie shooter. IMO, it is worth full price just from what I've played so far. The only gripe I have with the game is that in some of the levels the area is hard to navigate around, but that may be just my eyes tbh, all the levels are actually open and explorable for secrets and stuff, didn't run into any bugs so 9.5/10 game from me. Graphics aren't everything, kids."
,Recommended,281920,33525282,Posted: 13 July,all,ThePCGamer101,"DISCLAIMER: This is a full review, and NOT a first impressions review like all my other reviews, if you want a better full review, then please read better reviews then minePLEASE NOTE (2017): Due to recent false accusations of plagarism, I (the reviewer) would like to stress that all these reviews and upcoming reviews are original and are not blatantly copied. Other reviews are used to help stress my point across but are changed in such a way to make the review in my own wordingSplatter - Zombie Apocalypse or Blood Red Edition is a game developed and published by DreamworldsWhile the game feels a tad short, Splatter is just what it promises: a top down shooter with plenty to kill and some people to help or not along the wayConsidering its very low price it ended being quite a nice surprise. The story may be a bit exaggerated and the main character often feels cheesy from my own perspective but in the end what matters is that the game feels satisfying to playThe game can be finished in less than 5 hours depending on your chosen difficulty. If you want more out of the game after completing the main story there is also an arcade modeFor a small little indie game, it is quite an enjoyable game especially for it's asking price, I would highly recommend it to anyone!RECOMMENDED :)"
