,Recommended,281920,26155656,"Posted: 21 October, 2016",all,FuriousUnagi,"5 - Great4 - Good3 - Regular2 - Bad1 - TerribleSplatter - Blood Red Edition is a fun top-down-shooter with noir-like elements. If you're a fan of the genre, I'd say definately pick it up full price!The plot is linear, but it draws your attention enough so you want to keep playing to see what's up next. Although the plot is linear, the gameplay is not: sometimes you can make choices, even though they are minimal, and also can take on sidequests for some extra cash or ammo/loot -- there are not a lot of sidequests, but they are there to be completed.Enemy variety is not abundant, however, I think I like it that way; I mean, c'mon, it has zombies and its mutations and also some animal-ish mutations for good matter, what more can you want for a zombie shooter?Arcade survival mode is self-explanatory, always fun for some casual mindless shooting.I can say the game is polished enough, but there was one problem that made things difficult for me and even got me killed once. It started happening on the later stages: lightning effects issues. At first, it was just some crazy lightning effects -- like near a flame; but then it got to the point where I'd be in a dark room and my flashlight wouldn't work whatsoever! It's hard to explain, but the problem basically is: sometimes the game won't activate your flashlight because it thinks you're on a bright area, but you're not. You can see that's a glitch because, for the most part, the lightning effects are pretty satisfying for your eyes, but for the later stages, you might often see your character on a dark place without his flashlight on and some weird lightning effect dancing on your screen. Although that can get you killed, it's not a game-breaking issue by any means.That glitch aside, game's awesome. Acquiring and upgrading weapons is satisfying; shooting zombies is relaxing and fun. It's a good casual fun for fans of shooters and zombies."
