,Recommended,281920,33512773,Posted: 13 July,all,Rascilon,"Splatter - Zombie Apocalypse hits all the right notes for me.  It is a straight to the point top down twin stick zombie shooter.    What I appreciate most about the game is the inclusion of a casual difficulty level that makes it an accessible game for short play sessions.  The graphics are serviceable and appropriately gory.  The inclusion of trading cards and steam achievements, combined with the low price make this game a good buy for fans of casual games.  My only complaint about the title is the controller support could be improved.  While the controller does work, there are no on screen prompts and menu selection can be a bit wonky with the controller sticks.  Lastly, the steam overlay is supported making it easy to take and share screenshots on the steam playform.  For it's genre I would give the game a 4 out of 5."
