76561198086726380,Recommended,281920,26754702,"Posted: 22 November, 2016",all,HazyFogGlock,"Recommendedtl;drGame's fine. Decent graphics. Good amount of variety. Mostly fun shooting. Crappy story.Pros:Decent enemy variety: each enemy has an attack pattern (my favourite ones are the toadmen)You can mow down zombies with a threshing machine.Combat is fairly nuanced with different weapons fitting different situations.Advanced weapons have meaningful upgrades and feel satisfying to use.Gallons of blood and  hordes of enemies.The campaign manages to stay fresh thanks to sidemissions, a decent amount of exploration, various environments. It also introduces newer game mechanics (like fireflies) the more you progress into the game.When he's not trying to sound grim and somber and instead just acts all snarky, the main character is actually quite likable/funny.Graphically the game looks good enough with nice lighting effects, even though character models aren't great.Cons:Voice acting and story are utter trash. They are on the same level of the Alien Shooter series. You really don't care  about the other NPCs and are likely to skip their dialogues.Ammo is rare enough that you will be forced to use your basic pistol a lot. The pistol has infinite ammo and is somewhat efficient at killing most enemies. The problem is that it's just not that fun to shoot with.When your HP is low enough your view gets grayed out, until you find some (rare) health-pack. This is obnoxious because you can't see jackshit in this mode.The basic ubiquitous enemy zombies sport crappy uninspired models, bad animations and are generally unsatisfying to kill.Bosses are infamous bullet-sponges. They really take a million years to die, not fun at all."
